Here's the fixed Dockerfile:

<augment_code_snippet path="Dockerfile" mode="EDIT">
```dockerfile
FROM amazoncorretto:21 AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY . .
RUN chmod +x ./mvnw && sed -i 's/\r$//' ./mvnw && ./mvnw clean package -DskipTests

FROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```
</augment_code_snippet>

The fix adds:
- `chmod +x ./mvnw` - Makes the file executable
- `sed -i 's/\r$//' ./mvnw` - Removes Windows carriage return characters

**Alternative solution** - Copy `mvnw` separately with proper permissions:

<augment_code_snippet path="Dockerfile" mode="EDIT">
```dockerfile
FROM amazoncorretto:21 AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY --chmod=0755 mvnw mvnw
COPY .mvn/ .mvn/
COPY pom.xml .
COPY src/ src/
RUN ./mvnw clean package -DskipTests

FROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```
</augment_code_snippet>

This approach copies `mvnw` with executable permissions and avoids copying unnecessary files to the build context.
