:1,"type":0,"content":"The error shows that `tar` command is missing from the Amazon Corretto image. The Maven wrapper needs `tar` to extract Maven if it's not already installed. Here's the fix:

<augment_code_snippet path="Dockerfile" mode="EDIT">
```dockerfile
FROM amazoncorretto:21 AS build
WORKDIR /app

# Install tar which is required by Maven wrapper
RUN yum update -y && yum install -y tar gzip && yum clean all

COPY . .
RUN chmod +x ./mvnw && sed -i 's/\r$//' ./mvnw && ./mvnw clean package -DskipTests

FROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```
</augment_code_snippet>

**Alternative approach** - Use a base image that already has Maven installed:

<augment_code_snippet path="Dockerfile" mode="EDIT">
```dockerfile
FROM maven:3.9.4-amazoncorretto-21 AS build
WORKDIR /app
COPY pom.xml .
COPY src ./src
RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests

FROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```
</augment_code_snippet>

**Most efficient approach** - Multi-stage with dependency caching:

<augment_code_snippet path="Dockerfile" mode="EDIT">
```dockerfile
FROM maven:3.9.4-amazoncorretto-21 AS build
WORKDIR /app

# Copy pom.xml first for dependency caching
COPY pom.xml .
RUN mvn dependency:go-offline -B

# Copy source and build
COPY src ./src
RUN mvn clean package -DskipTests

FROM amazoncorretto:21-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080
ENTRYPOINT ["java", "-jar", "app.jar"]
```
</augment_code_snippet>

I recommend the last approach as it's more efficient and avoids the Maven wrapper issues entirely.
